  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Linking Newton research in Brazil, China and South Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As agreed in the original discussions around this element of the Urban Transformations programme three workshops are proposed; one each in Brazil, China and South Africa. We have involved partners in each of these countries in discussions over recent months to consider the most cost effective and high impact way we can do this with the limited resource available.  Three workshops are proposed in the three sites of Urban Transformations programme work that is Newton funded: Brazil, China, South Africa</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of the workshops is to showcase ESRC investments and partnerships in the countries engaged in the research, to develop links between British academics and scholars in Brazil, China and South Africa and to develop comparative and common themes of work on the Urban Transformations programme to maximize research academic and scholarly publication.</narrative>
  </description>
